Hadi accepted my request 7 minutes after receiving it, when I was really frustrated with the community. I have been at that point a 38-reference 100% confirmed/positive member, getting rejections from everyone (sometimes without even replying to my very detailed message). He was literally my last resort, and he didn't let me down.


This not only made my day, but also saved so many last-minute planning turmoil. He also accepted my friend who was not even mentioned in the request on a last-minute basis. He even ignored the fact that I didn't read the house rules before sending my request. I felt on the phone that I was talking to my brother!


He was such a caring host even though he was super busy over that weekend. He kept phoning me and asking if I needed anything. The apartment was very cozy and everything was there (he provides his guest with a separate apartment and hands them the keys!).


I'm going to Copenhagen again just to spend time with him!

Hadi is an awesome host and a cool guy. His home is very cozy and quiet where is easy to the center by bus and train.It's pity that he was little busy on his schedule due to my last minute request.Hopefully we will meet again in the future.thanks a lot bro.keep in touch

 He is a Teatcher so he is very calm and empathetic.

Hadi was great! He kept in touch promptly and met me at the apartment with dinner his mother had made.! The place is next to a beautiful park and not too far from the train station. Hope to see him again sometime , and would love to have him visit.

Hadi is the most thoughtful host I've met so far. He was always willing to help me out with anything that he could. I stayed at his apartment for four days in which there happened to be other couchsurfers staying as well, and Hadi would always ask me first if I was okay with having to share the place with other couchsurfers. He is a super kind and funny guy, very respectful and with no other intentions other than make friends from around the world and learn from their different cultures. I had a great time in Copenhagen, thank you very much for everything and hope to see you again soon! Best wishes :)

So far Hadi has been my favorite host! Cool guy, had a lot of fun with him. He let me stay in his extra apartment that he has, I would recommend staying with him if you can. Or even hanging out with him in copenhagen! Hadi, if you ever need a place to stay in the states, you're always welcome to my home! :)

Within a week I surfed Hadi's place again, he was welcoming as ever, we had some really great conversations together, about life in this world, food we eat and why we do things in different cultures that we do.

He was also hosting another surfer which meant we could also learn some more about South America! 

Hadi can also be your really great source of knowledge for Danish history and way of life, if you are seeking to go deeper than what you learn in a guided city tour!

Hadi is a great guy and you can feel it from the first moment. We didn't spend so much time, but you can feel the friendliness and the good vibe from the beginning!! :)
Thanks Hadi and see you around!! :)
Enjoy life!

Super fun host! I was supposed to arrive one day before, but something happened so have to go the next day. Hadi is super caring host. He even pick me up at the station. We had really good time hanging out together. One more thing, he literary give the whole place for me. The aparment is not in the city, but in really nice neighborhood. And you get to do what local do. I did my "pokemon" giant hunting around his neigborhood. I think that's like a must thing to do if you stay in his place. Thank you so much for having me Hadi! And see ya in Indonesia or maybe I will be back to Copenhagen!

After missing my flight out of CPH Hadi was more than happy to let me come stay another two nights. This time we got the chance to actually sit down and talk a little bit. He is a great guy and is chomping at the bit to help more couch surfers. When I was leaving he was already getting ready to host someone else. He is working a lot but despite spending so much time working he is always a phone call away and wants to know if there is anything that you might need. You could only hope to get a host like Hadi every time.

He had the app barely a week and he offered to myself and a backpacker from India to stay there simply because when he got back from abroad the previous renter had left the place alright, but not nice enough to rent. He had no idea who we were and had only just begun hosting but he reached out, and just gave me the keys. Technically I got them from the other backpacker when he left but he trusted two strangers enough to take his keys, stay, and leave with everything in tact and the keys on the counter. That takes optimism and trust you rarely find. While he was too busy to hang out it was not for lack of caring and I would absolutely come through Copenhagen to spend a proper day getting to know Copenhagen from him.

I was lucky, Hadi offered to host me really last minute and it turned out to be a really fun stay with him!

I was his first couchsurfing guest! He hosted me in his large apartment with a great view. I had it all by myself, he also trusted me with the house keys. It was all really comfortable!

He was very busy most of the weekend but he took out time to hangout. We played chess together (don't ask me who won :D), spent time driving around town and also wandered around in the cemetery, looking for H. C. Anderson's grave. He also took me to the best shawarma in town!

Hadi turned out to be an enigmatic man, being modest as he is, the profile doesn't brag much about him. But I prodded around a bit and turned out he's an upcoming YouTube star, an entrepreneur and also has a few cameos in Danish films as feathers to his hat!

Thank you for helping me have my hygge moment in Copenhagen! See you again!

I very much recommend Nick as a couchsurfing host, he is very thoughtful, friendly and kind. 
I stayed at his new place in Copenhagen and I really liked it, although he just moved in and had boxes around it still felt cozy in a nice scandinavian style:) 
Nick told me a lot interesting things about the Danish lifestyle. When we walked through the city, he put a lot of effort to explain me and my brother the buildings and history of copenhagen. 
We also went to the Reffen street food festival together (awesome!) and had some delicious international food together.
You picked the right guy for Copenhagen if you stay with him! 
Hope to see you again in Vienna, NicküôÇ
you are very welcome!

I had a really pleasant stay at Nick's place in Copenhagen :) He was very welcoming and nice! I really enjoyed chatting in the evening and watching TV, and talking about Danish culture and TV shows. And the cinnamon buns were delicious! Thanks a lot for hosting me and hope to meet you again :) good luck with your travels!

It was great to stay with Nick. Although it was a short visit, we got some time to hang out. He is very friendly and advised me on some spots to visit while he was at work. I had lots of flexibility to pace out my own plan. I would recommend anyone who visits Copenhagen to stay with him. Best wishes!! Cheers, mate!

Absolutely amazing family. So helpful with places to see and things to go do! 
Clean and cozy home and happy to hangout over dinner or let me chill out in peace. 
Looking forward to visiting again next year in summer time! Xo

Our stay with Dan, and his family was exceptional! We cannot express enough gratitude to them! The children were fantastic even though we only saw them for a short period. Their home was absolutely beautiful and Dan and Maja were beyond friendly, interesting and knowledgable. We were so lucky to have such great hosts. If you get the opportunity to stay with them you should cherish it and you will not be dissapointed!

My first couchsurfing was amazing!! It was really glad to meet Dan‚Äôs family. I was very lucky. He and Maya were very thoughtful and caring and have a big heart. I think they are the sweetest people in Denmark üá©üá∞ ;)
They really welcomed us and gave us a fabulous hospitality. We respected to each other as his family has a busy lifestyle and we left home by noon and back home at midnight. There was no disturbance at all. Dan gave us a practical tips and Maya always showed us her warmth. 

Their house was really beautiful and spacious. The room we stayed in was very cozy and tidy as well(it was perfect for two people). They have a back yard too and we could see ducks, chickens or small stream and so on. Very eco-friendly environment. It‚Äôs located a bit out of town but close enough to commute. There is a train station nearby and it takes 20-25mins into citycentre.

I had the best time in Denmark and I‚Äôm genuinely grateful to Dan and Maya so much ‚ù§Ô∏è 

Thanks Dan, Maya (take care Ellen, Alfred)

I stayed at Dan's family place for 2 nights. 

It was really enjoyable. I can recommend the family, Dan and his wife were very welcoming since the beginning. They are very flexible, and I didn't lack of anything. 
The location is not in Copenhagen itself, but in a close suburb. However it was a very lovely and peaceful place, and it was very easy to reach Copenhagen by train.

I would come back there another time, and wish them a lot of success.

Dan is a great host and a person! He is very friendly and knowledgeable. His family is really nice) My friend Paul and I were living in a separate room of his green house üè° , probably "the most most green house in Vallensbek"))) It was very clean and comfortable)) 
Dan gave us few tips about interesting places in Copenhagen and transportation system, which were really useful. 
Also Dan is a responsible person, who thinks about the environment. He is always ready to face new challenges and learn - it's great! 

It was a pleasure to stay at Dan's house for 2 days!
I strongly recommend Dan as a host and as a guest!

Cya somewhere,
Mike and Paul

What can I say? 

I just left Dan and Maja's home this morning and I miss it with all my heart! Anyone who has the pleasure of staying with this wonderful family will be eternally grateful.

It was my first time to do couchsurfing. I definitely would not like to generalize and judge her hospitability with my experience, but for now I‚Äôm describing mine. I with my friend was supposed to stay for 2 nights in Denmark. Before coming we had nice conversations and arranged some plans. We arrived early morning and spend all day in the city; it was nice of her to pick up us to her place with the car. Until that everything was smooth, we were sharing experiences, etc. The fact that made us not stay for the second night was her ‚Äòrequest‚Äô to carry a big couch for about 1 km to her house. We were really tired that day and still had to spend our whole next day walking, so we refused. Her attitude afterwards wasn‚Äôt pleasant at all and I consider that trying to take advantage of us is not this community‚Äôs goal. As for me, I tried to do my best to not complicate the situation; we cooked, did the dishes and even cleaned the cooker (even if it was dirty before). It is really hard to stay in a place where you do not feel honestly welcomed. Id strongly believe it could happen to anyone to have a bad day, but treating someone unfairly while you‚Äôve subscribed for taking part in this kind of program makes me think that everyone is always doing a favor while demanding for smth in return. I‚Äôd still keep on trying this option of travelling, as I‚Äôd not like at all leaving everything with a one-sided story.

We stayed with Josefine one night with my girlfriend. I wouldn't recommend her as a host. When we arrived she offered us to play card game later and we agreed. I smelled that she drank alcohol, probably she was not sober.  So there was another girl in the kitchen (Josefine's housemate's surfer), they were chatting there, so we joined. After some time Josefine left, we stayed there and continued chatting. She was cooking, and I thought we are gonna wait her and play together. After one hour Josefine just appeared and started complaining about that she was waiting for us in the living room and we didn't joined. If she wants something, she should let us know, I'm not a mind-reader, and I'm not gonna follow anybody to check what she is doing. Other day we apologized and left.

We came to Josefine's place and there was already another couchsurfer Kari, and Josefine offered to play cards. We agreed, and after some time she went to kitchen and started talking with Kari about USA and Danish politics, we joined them and stayed there, and after some time she just left kitchen. We stayed with Kari and continued talking while she was cooking and after one hour Josefine approached me and said: "you are guys not nice, I offered you to play cards and I was waiting for you for 2 hours, while you all were talking in the kitchen". I apologized and said that we had no idea why she left the kitchen, probably she wanted to do something herself, on what she replied: "do not pretend that you didn't know that. Of course I'm not going to kick you out now, but couchsurfing is not about free bed" after that she turned off lights everywhere and behaved like dictator, what made us feel really uncomfortable. In the morning we apologized again all together and left.

text: Jo was fantastic! Her home was lovely and her roommates were all great! Our first day she drove out to visit a castle with us and that night we all cooked and ate together.  She was even nice enough to lend us her train card which saved us a lot of money.  She's very easy going and has a lot of great stories and the world's cutest, sassiest dog.  I definitely recommend staying with her!

Staying with Jo was one of the most welcoming CS experiences I've had so far; when you meet her it feels like you've known her for years! My friend and I stayed with her for three nights, and on the first day she drove us out to a castle we had mentioned wanting to see and spent the day exploring with us. We loved staying outside of the hustle and bustle of Copenhagen in Vekso, which was quiet and beautiful, and Jo's house is wonderful as well. She is (as are each of her housemates!) a fun, friendly, and caring person with incredible stories and a true love and interest for the humans she encounters. Jo, you are always welcome in the States or the UK or wherever Sarah or I happen to be-- hopefully I will see you again in my travels soon (not kidding, let's do something before I leave Europe!) !! (And CSers, her dog is the best dog in the history of the world. Obsessed.)

Unfortunately the sharehouse WiFi was quite illusive (I never found it).

Josephine was also flexible when our plans changed and we left sooner than we had planned.

It was my first couchsurfing experience and I loved it. Jo has an incredible house, amazing flatmates (special mention to Nuno) and a lovely dog! I really loved the experience and would most definitely reccomend her!
Josefine was great host. The house was beautiful place to stay. We were happy to spend evening with all her housemates and we had lot of fun. Thank you for your time :) :) :)

Josefine's big house is always full of CouchSurfers, and she says that she has slowed down a lot from when she started! Hard to imagine what it must have been like before. Because of this, it very much has a kind of hostel vibe to it. That could be good or bad depending on what you are looking for from CouchSurfing. On the one hand, you have the opportunity to meet other CSers and do things together, which I did during my stay, on the other hand if you like to connect with or get to know your hosts, don't go in expecting that. It's great that Josefine accepts requests from almost everyone, male or female, solo travelers or couples, experienced surfers or newbies, I think she wants to give back to the CS community and considers it a bit of public service, but I don't really know, we didn't get to know each other very well. For me that was the biggest downside.

Josefine was really helpful accommodating me near Copenhagen when all hostels were booked. She makes sure everyone has their place to sleep, runs the house very organized so that everyone can have a good experience.

This was my first couchsurfing experience and I thank her so much in welcoming me and sharing her experiences while I had a new peofile, and also for creating an environment where you meet lots of other couchsurfers.

The world needs more people like Josefine that actually wants to give back and help as many as she can.

If you're ever in Brazil Josefine, please tell me so I can help you in the best way I can.

Definitely the most funny walk ever! I'm so glad that i had the chance to get this amazing and really authentic experience of Denmark. 

Thanks a lot, Claus!

#antihygge :D

Claus offers a completely unique and analytical perspective on the world. Although the actual time we spent together was short, our conversations were incredibly thought provoking and intellectually stimulating.  I can honestly say that his perspective on life has inspired me in more ways than one. His generosity, selflessness, and trust in the world around him is something that I will never forget. Whoever has the opportunity to meet Claus is in for a wonderful surprise. Thanks again!

Claus is a very talkative man who has a lot of stories to share. There was a heavy rain in Copenhagen when I arrived so unfortunately it was very difficult to explore the city with that weather conditions. I met with Claus in the evening and he showed me some very nice places of the city. Unfortunately, his car had broken down so we couldn't see a lot of attractions but anyway we had a really nice talks. 
Then we went to his place and he shared with me some drinks. He is an extremely active person and likes spending time outdoors but the weather didn't allow us to do a lot. But anyway, in the morning we took a trolley near IKEA and he drove me to the station and that was a real fun. 
I hope the next time I will be in Copenhagen we can meet up again and do much more things together.

Claus is active and loves adventure along with being musically skilled. He is sure to show you the spots in and around Copenhagen that you are interested in. Thanks again for showing me parts of Denmark I would have otherwise never even known about! Cheers- Cat

Claus is full of energy and spirit! He has some crazy travel stories he'll share with you too. Interesting guy with a positive outlook. Thank you for showing me the city, the beach, and for letting me use your roller skates!

Claus was really really helpful! His knowledges about Copenhagen and suburbs made my staying there so cool! He's a big fan of spontaneous traveling and doing outdoor activities, so, if you like it, then Claus is a perfect host for you :)

Claus is the amazing host who I have not met in real person. But he left me with the key without a doubt - this is the first time I've experienced couchsurfing without seeing host in real! It's really a matter of trust. But I have to apologize that I accidentally broke a glass while cooking. I felt so sorry about that. I still appreciate him letting me stay. If there is second chance again, I hope to meet and chat with Claus in real person !

Claus spent tons of time and showed me much of Copenhagen. He is interested in deeper conversation, and likes to always stay active and doing things (which I am the same way though had hurt my foot and wasn't able to keep up!). I wish you the best, and hope you get to travel Europe this summer!

Despite being short and me being away for easter time almost all the time it was nice hosting Pia. I had no second though about giving her the key of the house. She's very friendly as well an left some beer in the fridge ;) I would definitely host her again.

Pia, you are an amazing guest. You are very friendly and a good cook üôÇ. We  enjoyed your company and had good chats. If you ever come back to belgium, we would glad to be your host again. Hopefully we can one day dive toghether. That would be fun. Good luck on your future trips.

I really enjoyed having you over Pia! You are very low maintenance and I even felt a little uncomfortable seeing you do the dishes straight away, taken my house rules to leave dishes at least for a week :) Thanks so much for the Danish beers (still enjoying them), the whiskey (you shouldn't have..) and the new kitchen utensil. It is scary :)

Hope you enjoyed the man-cave!
Pia is a great host. She was so friendly to show me a nice road to drive with the motorcycle. We had pleasant and interesting conversation. She really made me feel at home. Thanks Pia!

I stayed Pia at 1 night..she picked me up from at train station, her house is situated in countryside near fijord..she gave me a guestroom and it was so comfortable, she is a definition local, she adviced me places, and her garden..amazing i spent some time at there..i felt so freshing..
  She is so kind and welcoming person.of course I recommend , next time i plan to come again and help her garden work and wall painting,;)

Hi there hopefully you are doing well. Thank you so much for having you around the world and I hope you enjoyed this time here in Africa and you are more than welcome back again and thank you for being you have a good time

text:
As soon as Pia got out of her car to welcome me, I had a subconscious feeling that she was an open-minded, sweet, caring and generous person. And after a short time, I felt already at home. She gave me a full room with private bathroom!
She offered a short trip to the castle in Helsingor and along the route, we had dinner.
Pia, thanks for the nice conversations and hospitality. It's a pity I could stay only one night and you had to work during the day. I certainly come back once in the future (weekend?)!
Recommended host for sure!

We enjoyed staying with Anne and Kurt.   It was just like going home!  Anne is so generous,  thoughtful and caring,  Kurt is carefree and loves a good laugh.  We shared cooking and had lots of deep and meaningful conversations.  We were totally inspired by their travel stories and photos!   The house is very clean and very beautiful and there are lots of animals,  both domestic and wild in the back yard.  The nights were quiet with no traffic noise.

Great stay with Anne and Kurt. Beautiful home, good location, fantastic garden. Liked Anton the cat plus others in the menagerie. Great cycle ride into fredrickssund, welcome and plentiful hospitality. Would have been happy to stay longer but when i had only 10 days to see the whole of Denmark had to limit my stay to 24 hours.
fromPublicAddressDescriptionfromAvatarUr: Hemel Hempstead, England, United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland

text: Anne and Kurt are hospitable, open-minded and considerate people and I felt myself very confortable at their home in the south of Frederikssund. They made a very good meal for me and we talked a lot about different things. They gave me a tiny little room an a quite good bed. Their house is such a nice place to calme down and to relax. And the cykling route 40 passes by. I enjoyed the time with them and recommend them highly as hosts.

Anne, Kurt, and their extended feathered family provided one of my comfiest couch surfing experiences to date.  I was on a bicycle trip around Zealand and was looking for a place to slow down for a day, the refuge of Anne's hospitality and cozy home surrounded by the tranquility of a lovingly tended garden sucked me in and made it difficult to get back on my bike. We went hunting for finds in the local bounty of thrift stores, I was included in an evening of square dancing, and yummy cake and meals were shared. I highly recommend popping by for a visit to this countryside gem, and I hope to have the opportunity to reciprocate in the future. Wishing you all the best!

Anne and Kurt are simply amazing hosts! They are helpful, friendly, hospitable and really interesting company. Already before the Start of my trip, Anne sent me some usefull information about getting around in Denmark. Their house with the amazing garden is an outstanding experience for itself! I can truely say the evening I spent together with both of them over good food and interesting conversations next to the campfire was one of the best evenings I had during my trip in Denmark!
fromPublicAddressDescriptionfromAvatarUr: Southampton, England, United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland

text: Anne and Kurt are wonderful hosts and represent the best of CS and the best of Denmark! Thoughtful, generous, helpful - we have been spoiled by them! A half-hour's train ride from Copenhagen, their country home (complete with bucolic scenery, quiet, and ducks) is a great place to rest and share laughs after a day in the city or on the road. Thank you also for introducing us to the stevia plant - herb tea from fresh picked herbs is wonderful!

Anne and Kurt are very, very, very nice people who host me for one night, we talk about a lot of topics and eat A LOT but amazing food that they cooked. 
I thought losing some weight during my trip but not haha. I slept in a very comfortable bed, i was very difficult to wake up after this night. 
I lost my towel in a previous couchsurfing and they gave it to me an another one (it will be back soon) and some apples for my trip. It was an amazing experience for my first couchsurfing so thank you so much !

text: Jo√£o is such a great guy! He is always incredibly happy, funny and very optimist, even during the morning. He is the kind of person who sees people's best, and always has good stories to tell. He is the best companionship I could have. See you soon, bonito.

Jo√£o and his wife Ida were very kind to us. They can tell a lot of interesting stories about different places in world,  we learned for example about Japan and Greenland. Joao likes to laugh a lot, he answered our hundred questions patiently.  He showed us his favourite place in Kopenhagen, a board game caf√© which is a nice place with awesome hot chocolate, you will enjoy it even if you don't like board games that much :-)

Jo√£o did his best to keep track of our impossible planning to make sure we get home to an open door without problems. Home is a collective of 9 young people that dumpster dive and try to live in a more sustainable way, enjoy the forest close to the house and the company of each other - a nice place to be in! Thank you a lot for hosting us and wishing both of you all the best!

Had to bring a cotton candy machine to a friends birthday, so I couldn't welcome them personally. I only met them in the morning for a short while before going to work. Very friendly, polite and grateful people. It made me really happy to see that my houseboat made their day happier ^_^ Keep in touch! See you in Denmark maybe :D

This person is irresponsible. I do not know how he was able to host tourists with such an attitude. He did not answer my calls when I arrived in Copenhagen. Have in mind. It is best to have several more options for overnight accommodation

Though our stay was very brief, we had good fun with Christopher and were very comfortable at his place. Christopher is friendly, knowledgeable, and generous‚Äîmany thanks!!

Max and his lovely cousin Louise have hosted me on two different occasions, once when I gave them WAAAY to much notice (about three months) and once when I have them about two days. On my first trip Lousie made me feel really welcome, gave me great recommendations on how to make the best of my short stay in Copenhagen, made me cups of delicious tea and lent me a very useful map. On my second trip even though I was held up by transport and arrived late, Max and Lousie were really understanding and still made me feel like a welcome surfer and not a burden. I wish I could have spent more time staying with them, and if I ever go back to Copenhagen I would definately want to stay with them again. PERFECT hosts.
